{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I want to start off by saying, Houston, we have a problem."},{"time":5000,"text":"We're entering a second generation of no progress"},{"time":9000,"text":"in terms of human flight in space. In fact, we've regressed."},{"time":14000,"text":"We stand a very big chance of losing our ability to inspire our youth"},{"time":20000,"text":"to go out and continue this very important thing"},{"time":23000,"text":"that we as a species have always done."},{"time":25000,"text":"And that is, instinctively we've gone out"},{"time":28000,"text":"and climbed over difficult places, went to more hostile places,"},{"time":34000,"text":"and found out later, maybe to our surprise, that that's the reason we survived."},{"time":40000,"text":"And I feel very strongly"},{"time":42000,"text":"that it's not good enough for us to have generations of kids"},{"time":46000,"text":"that think that it's OK to look forward to a better version"},{"time":50000,"text":"of a cell phone with a video in it."},{"time":53000,"text":"They need to look forward to exploration; they need to look forward to colonization;"},{"time":57000,"text":"they need to look forward to breakthroughs."},{"time":61000,"text":"We need to inspire them, because they need to lead us"},{"time":65000,"text":"and help us survive in the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68000,"text":"I'm particularly troubled that what NASA's doing right now with this new Bush doctrine"},{"time":74000,"text":"to -- for this next decade and a half -- oh shoot, I screwed up."},{"time":80000,"text":"We have real specific instructions here not to talk about politics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":86000,"text":"What we're looking forward to is --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":89000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":90000,"text":"what we're looking forward to"},{"time":93000,"text":"is not only the inspiration of our children,"},{"time":96000,"text":"but the current plan right now is not really even allowing"},{"time":101000,"text":"the most creative people in this country -- the Boeing's and Lockheed's"},{"time":105000,"text":"space engineers -- to go out and take risks and try new stuff."},{"time":111000,"text":"We're going to go back to the moon ... 50 years later?"},{"time":117000,"text":"And we're going to do it very specifically planned to not learn anything new."},{"time":123000,"text":"I'm really troubled by that. But anyway that's --"},{"time":127000,"text":"the basis of the thing that I want to share with you today, though,"},{"time":131000,"text":"is that right back to where we inspire people"},{"time":135000,"text":"who will be our great leaders later."},{"time":137000,"text":"That's the theme of my next 15 minutes here."},{"time":141000,"text":"And I think that the inspiration begins when you're very young:\n"},{"time":145000,"text":"three-year-olds, up to 12-, 14-year-olds."},{"time":149000,"text":"What they look at is the most important thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":153000,"text":"Let's take a snapshot at aviation."},{"time":156000,"text":"And there was a wonderful little short four-year time period"},{"time":159000,"text":"when marvelous things happened."},{"time":162000,"text":"It started in 1908, when the Wright brothers flew in Paris, and everybody said,"},{"time":166000,"text":"\"Ooh, hey, I can do that.\" There's only a few people that have flown"},{"time":170000,"text":"in early 1908. In four years, 39 countries had hundreds of airplanes,"},{"time":175000,"text":"thousand of pilots. Airplanes were invented by natural selection."},{"time":179000,"text":"Now you can say that intelligent design designs our airplanes of today,"},{"time":183000,"text":"but there was no intelligent design really designing those early airplanes."},{"time":187000,"text":"There were probably at least 30,000 different things tried,"},{"time":192000,"text":"and when they crash and kill the pilot, don't try that again."},{"time":196000,"text":"The ones that flew and landed OK"},{"time":199000,"text":"because there were no trained pilots"},{"time":200000,"text":"who had good flying qualities by definition."},{"time":204000,"text":"So we, by making a whole bunch of attempts, thousands of attempts,"},{"time":209000,"text":"in that four-year time period, we invented the concepts"},{"time":212000,"text":"of the airplanes that we fly today. And that's why they're so safe,"},{"time":215000,"text":"as we gave it a lot of chance to find what's good."},{"time":219000,"text":"That has not happened at all in space flying."},{"time":221000,"text":"There's only been two concepts tried -- two by the U.S. and one by the Russians."}]},{"cues":[{"time":225000,"text":"Well, who was inspired during that time period?"},{"time":227000,"text":"Aviation Week asked me to make a list of who I thought"},{"time":230000,"text":"were the movers and shakers of the first 100 years of aviation."},{"time":233000,"text":"And I wrote them down and I found out later that every one of them"},{"time":237000,"text":"was a little kid in that wonderful renaissance of aviation."},{"time":244000,"text":"Well, what happened when I was a little kid was -- some pretty heavy stuff too."},{"time":248000,"text":"The jet age started: the missile age started. Von Braun was on there"},{"time":253000,"text":"showing how to go to Mars -- and this was before Sputnik."},{"time":255000,"text":"And this was at a time when Mars was a hell of a lot more interesting"},{"time":259000,"text":"than it is now. We thought there'd be animals there;"},{"time":261000,"text":"we knew there were plants there; the colors change, right?"},{"time":265000,"text":"But, you know, NASA screwed that up because they've sent these robots"},{"time":268000,"text":"and they've landed it only in the deserts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":275000,"text":"If you look at what happened -- this little black line is as fast as man ever flew,"},{"time":282000,"text":"and the red line is top-of-the-line military fighters"},{"time":285000,"text":"and the blue line is commercial air transport."},{"time":288000,"text":"You notice here's a big jump when I was a little kid --"},{"time":290000,"text":"and I think that had something to do with giving me the courage"},{"time":294000,"text":"to go out and try something that other people weren't having the courage to try."},{"time":299000,"text":"Well, what did I do when I was a kid?"},{"time":301000,"text":"I didn't do the hotrods and the girls and the dancing"},{"time":304000,"text":"and, well, we didn't have drugs in those days. But I did competition model airplanes."},{"time":309000,"text":"I spent about seven years during the Vietnam War"},{"time":311000,"text":"flight-testing airplanes for the Air Force."},{"time":314000,"text":"And then I went in and I had a lot of fun building airplanes"},{"time":316000,"text":"that people could build in their garages."},{"time":319000,"text":"And some 3,000 of those are flying. Of course, one of them"},{"time":322000,"text":"is around the world Voyager. I founded another company in '82,"},{"time":326000,"text":"which is my company now."},{"time":328000,"text":"And we have developed more than one new type of airplane every year since 1982."},{"time":335000,"text":"And there's a lot of them that I actually can't show you on this chart."}]},{"cues":[{"time":339000,"text":"The most impressive airplane ever, I believe, was designed"},{"time":343000,"text":"only a dozen years after the first operational jet."},{"time":347000,"text":"Stayed in service till it was too rusty to fly, taken out of service."},{"time":351000,"text":"We retreated in '98 back to something that was developed in '56. What?"},{"time":358000,"text":"The most impressive spaceship ever, I believe,"},{"time":361000,"text":"was a Grumman Lunar Lander. It was a -- you know, it landed on the moon,"},{"time":366000,"text":"take off of the moon, didn't need any maintenance guys --"},{"time":368000,"text":"that's kind of cool."},{"time":370000,"text":"We've lost that capability. We abandoned it in '72."},{"time":373000,"text":"This thing was designed three years after Gagarin first flew in space in 1961."},{"time":378000,"text":"Three years, and we can't do that now. Crazy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":383000,"text":"Talk very briefly about innovation cycles, things that grow,"},{"time":388000,"text":"have a lot of activity; they die out when they're replaced by something else."},{"time":392000,"text":"These things tend to happen every 25 years."},{"time":395000,"text":"40 years long, with an overlap. You can put that statement"},{"time":399000,"text":"on all kinds of different technologies. The interesting thing --"},{"time":402000,"text":"by the way, the speed here, excuse me, higher-speed travel"},{"time":405000,"text":"is the title of these innovation cycles. There is none here."},{"time":411000,"text":"These two new airplanes are the same speed as the DC8 that was done in 1958."},{"time":419000,"text":"Here's the biggie, and that is, you don't have innovation cycles"},{"time":422000,"text":"if the government develops and the government uses it."},{"time":425000,"text":"You know, a good example, of course, is the DARPA net."},{"time":429000,"text":"Computers were used for artillery first, then IRS."},{"time":432000,"text":"But when we got it, now you have all the level of activity,"},{"time":435000,"text":"all the benefit from it. Private sector has to do it."},{"time":439000,"text":"Keep that in mind. I put down innovation --"},{"time":442000,"text":"I've looked for innovation cycles in space; I found none."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445000,"text":"The very first year, starting when Gagarin went in space,"},{"time":449000,"text":"and a few weeks later Alan Shepherd, there were five manned"},{"time":452000,"text":"space flights in the world -- the very first year."},{"time":455000,"text":"In 2003, everyone that the United States sent to space was killed."},{"time":464000,"text":"There were only three or four flights in 2003."},{"time":466000,"text":"In 2004, there were only two flights: two Russian Soyuz flights"},{"time":473000,"text":"to the international manned station. And I had to fly three in Mojave"},{"time":477000,"text":"with my little group of a couple dozen people"},{"time":479000,"text":"in order to get to a total of five,"},{"time":481000,"text":"which was the number the same year back in 1961."},{"time":486000,"text":"There is no growth. There's no activity. There's no nothing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":491000,"text":"This is a picture here taken from SpaceShipOne."},{"time":494000,"text":"This is a picture here taken from orbit."},{"time":496000,"text":"Our goal is to make it so that you can see this picture and really enjoy that."},{"time":502000,"text":"We know how to do it for sub-orbital flying now, do it safe enough --"},{"time":506000,"text":"at least as safe as the early airlines -- so that can be done."},{"time":510000,"text":"And I think I want to talk a little bit about why we had the courage"},{"time":515000,"text":"to go out and try that as a small company."}]},{"cues":[{"time":522000,"text":"Well, first of all, what's going to happen next?"},{"time":525000,"text":"The first industry will be a high volume, a lot of players."},{"time":529000,"text":"There's another one announced just last week."},{"time":532000,"text":"And it will be sub-orbital. And the reason it has to be sub-orbital"},{"time":538000,"text":"is, there is not solutions for adequate safety"},{"time":541000,"text":"to fly the public to orbit. The governments have been doing this --"},{"time":546000,"text":"three governments have been doing this for 45 years,"},{"time":548000,"text":"and still four percent of the people that have left the atmosphere have died."},{"time":552000,"text":"That's -- You don't want to run a business with that kind of a safety record."},{"time":557000,"text":"It'll be very high volume; we think 100,000 people will fly by 2020."},{"time":563000,"text":"I can't tell you when this will start,"},{"time":565000,"text":"because I don't want my competition to know my schedule."},{"time":568000,"text":"But I think once it does, we will find solutions,"},{"time":573000,"text":"and very quickly, you'll see those resort hotels in orbit."},{"time":576000,"text":"And that real easy thing to do, which is a swing around the moon"},{"time":579000,"text":"so you have this cool view. And that will be really cool."},{"time":583000,"text":"Because the moon doesn't have an atmosphere --"},{"time":585000,"text":"you can do an elliptical orbit and miss it by 10 feet if you want."},{"time":588000,"text":"Oh, it's going to be so much fun."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":592000,"text":"OK. My critics say, \"Hey, Rutan's just spending"},{"time":596000,"text":"a lot of these billionaires' money for joyrides for billionaires."},{"time":601000,"text":"What's this? This is not a transportation system; it's just for fun.\""},{"time":606000,"text":"And I used to be bothered by that, and then I got to thinking,"},{"time":609000,"text":"well, wait a minute. I bought my first Apple computer in 1978"},{"time":614000,"text":"and I bought it because I could say, \"I got a computer at my house and you don't."},{"time":620000,"text":"'What do you use it for?' Come over. It does Frogger.\" OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":625000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":626000,"text":"Not the bank's computer or Lockheed's computer,"},{"time":629000,"text":"but the home computer was for games."},{"time":632000,"text":"For a whole decade it was for fun -- we didn't even know what it was for."},{"time":636000,"text":"But what happened, the fact that we had this big industry,"},{"time":640000,"text":"big development, big improvement and capability and so on,"},{"time":644000,"text":"and they get out there in enough homes -- we were ripe for a new invention."},{"time":649000,"text":"And the inventor is in this audience."},{"time":651000,"text":"Al Gore invented the Internet and because of that,"},{"time":655000,"text":"something that we used for a whole year -- excuse me --"},{"time":658000,"text":"a whole decade for fun, became everything -- our commerce, our research,"},{"time":664000,"text":"our communication and, if we let the Google guys"},{"time":668000,"text":"think for another couple weekends, we can add a dozen more things to the list. (Laughter)"},{"time":672000,"text":"And it won't be very long before you won't be able to convince kids"},{"time":675000,"text":"that we didn't always have computers in our homes."},{"time":680000,"text":"So fun is defendable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":683000,"text":"OK, I want to show you kind of a busy chart,"},{"time":688000,"text":"but in it is my prediction with what's going to happen."},{"time":691000,"text":"And in it also brings up another point, right here."},{"time":695000,"text":"There's a group of people that have come forward --"},{"time":699000,"text":"and you don't know all of them -- but the ones that have come forward"},{"time":702000,"text":"were inspired as young children, this little three- to 15-year-old age,"},{"time":709000,"text":"by us going to orbit and going to the moon here,"},{"time":712000,"text":"right in this time period."},{"time":714000,"text":"Paul Allen, Elan Musk, Richard Branson, Jeff Bezos, the Ansari family,"},{"time":724000,"text":"which is now funding the Russians' sub-orbital thing,"},{"time":729000,"text":"Bob Bigelow, a private space station, and Carmack."},{"time":733000,"text":"These people are taking money and putting it in an interesting area,"},{"time":739000,"text":"and I think it's a lot better than they put it in an area"},{"time":742000,"text":"of a better cell phone or something -- but they're putting it in very --"},{"time":746000,"text":"areas and this will lead us into this kind of capability,"},{"time":750000,"text":"and it will lead us into the next really big thing"},{"time":752000,"text":"and it will allow us to explore. And I think eventually"},{"time":756000,"text":"it will allow us to colonize and to keep us from going extinct."}]},{"cues":[{"time":760000,"text":"They were inspired by big progress. But look at the progress that's going on after that."},{"time":766000,"text":"There were a couple of examples here."},{"time":768000,"text":"The military fighters had a -- highest-performance military airplane"},{"time":772000,"text":"was the SR71. It went a whole life cycle, got too rusty to fly,"},{"time":777000,"text":"and was taken out of service. The Concorde doubled the speed for airline travel."},{"time":782000,"text":"It went a whole life cycle without competition,"},{"time":785000,"text":"took out of service. And we're stuck back here"},{"time":788000,"text":"with the same kind of capability for military fighters"},{"time":791000,"text":"and commercial airline travel that we had back in the late '50s."}]},{"cues":[{"time":795000,"text":"But something is out there to inspire our kids now."},{"time":799000,"text":"And I'm talking about if you've got a baby now,"},{"time":801000,"text":"or if you've got a 10-year-old now."},{"time":802000,"text":"What's out there is there's something really interesting going to happen here."},{"time":808000,"text":"Relatively soon, you'll be able to buy a ticket"},{"time":810000,"text":"and fly higher and faster than the highest-performance"},{"time":815000,"text":"military operational airplane. It's never happened before."},{"time":819000,"text":"The fact that they have stuck here with this kind of performance"},{"time":824000,"text":"has been, well, you know, you win the war in 12 minutes;"},{"time":827000,"text":"why do you need something better?"},{"time":828000,"text":"But I think when you guys start buying tickets and flying"},{"time":831000,"text":"sub-orbital flights to space, very soon -- wait a minute,"},{"time":836000,"text":"what's happening here, we'll have military fighters"},{"time":839000,"text":"with sub-orbital capability, and I think very soon this."},{"time":842000,"text":"But the interesting thing about it is the commercial guys are going to go first."},{"time":846000,"text":"OK, I look forward to a new \"capitalist's space race,\" let's call it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":852000,"text":"You remember the space race in the '60s was for national prestige,"},{"time":856000,"text":"because we lost the first two milestones."},{"time":859000,"text":"We didn't lose them technically. The fact that we had the hardware"},{"time":863000,"text":"to put something in orbit when we let Von Braun fly it --"},{"time":868000,"text":"you can argue that's not a technical loss."},{"time":870000,"text":"Sputnik wasn't a technical loss, but it was a prestige loss."},{"time":874000,"text":"America -- the world saw America as not being the leader in technology,"},{"time":881000,"text":"and that was a very strong thing."},{"time":883000,"text":"And then we flew Alan Shepherd weeks after Gagarin,"},{"time":888000,"text":"not months or decades, or whatever. So we had the capability."},{"time":893000,"text":"But America lost. We lost. And because of that, we made a big jump to recover it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":902000,"text":"Well, again, what's interesting here is we've lost"},{"time":905000,"text":"to the Russians on the first couple of milestones already."},{"time":908000,"text":"You cannot buy a ticket commercially to fly into space in America --"},{"time":913000,"text":"can't do it. You can buy it in Russia."},{"time":918000,"text":"You can fly with Russian hardware. This is available"},{"time":921000,"text":"because a Russian space program is starving,"},{"time":924000,"text":"and it's nice for them to get 20 million here and there to take one of the seats."},{"time":929000,"text":"It's commercial. It can be defined as space tourism. They are also offering a trip"},{"time":936000,"text":"to go on this whip around the moon, like Apollo 8 was done."},{"time":940000,"text":"100 million bucks -- hey, I can go to the moon."},{"time":943000,"text":"But, you know, would you have thought back in the '60s,"},{"time":946000,"text":"when the space race was going on,"},{"time":948000,"text":"that the first commercial capitalist-like thing to do"},{"time":954000,"text":"to buy a ticket to go to the moon would be in Russian hardware?"},{"time":958000,"text":"And would you have thought, would the Russians have thought,"},{"time":961000,"text":"that when they first go to the moon in their developed hardware,"},{"time":965000,"text":"the guys inside won't be Russians? Maybe it'll probably be a Japanese"},{"time":969000,"text":"or an American billionaire? Well, that's weird: you know, it really is."},{"time":973000,"text":"But anyway, I think we need to beat them again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":977000,"text":"I think what we'll do is we'll see a successful, very successful,"},{"time":984000,"text":"private space flight industry. Whether we're first or not really doesn't matter."},{"time":989000,"text":"The Russians actually flew a supersonic transport before the Concorde."},{"time":995000,"text":"And then they flew a few cargo flights, and took it out of service."},{"time":999000,"text":"I think you kind of see the same kind of parallel"},{"time":1002000,"text":"when the commercial stuff is offered."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1006000,"text":"OK, we'll talk just a little bit about commercial development for human space flight."},{"time":1010000,"text":"This little thing says here: five times"},{"time":1012000,"text":"what NASA's doing by 2020. I want to tell you, already"},{"time":1020000,"text":"there's about 1.5 billion to 1.7 billion"},{"time":1024000,"text":"investment in private space flight that is not government at all --"},{"time":1030000,"text":"already, worldwide. If you read -- if you Google it,"},{"time":1035000,"text":"you'll find about half of that money, but there's twice of that"},{"time":1038000,"text":"being committed out there -- not spent yet, but being committed"},{"time":1042000,"text":"and planned for the next few years. Hey, that's pretty big."},{"time":1045000,"text":"I'm predicting, though, as profitable as this industry is going to be --"},{"time":1050000,"text":"and it certainly is profitable when you fly people at 200,000 dollars"},{"time":1054000,"text":"on something that you can actually operate at a tenth of that cost,"},{"time":1058000,"text":"or less -- this is going to be very profitable."},{"time":1062000,"text":"I predict, also, that the investment that will flow into this"},{"time":1065000,"text":"will be somewhere around half of what the U.S. taxpayer"},{"time":1069000,"text":"spends for NASA's manned spacecraft work."},{"time":1073000,"text":"And every dollar that flows into that will be spent more efficiently"},{"time":1078000,"text":"by a factor of 10 to 15. And what that means is before we know it,"},{"time":1086000,"text":"the progress in human space flight, with no taxpayer dollars,"},{"time":1093000,"text":"will be at a level of about five times as much"},{"time":1099000,"text":"as the current NASA budgets for human space flight."},{"time":1104000,"text":"And that is because it's us. It's private industry."},{"time":1112000,"text":"You should never depend on the government to do this sort of stuff --"},{"time":1118000,"text":"and we've done it for a long time. The NACA, before NASA,"},{"time":1121000,"text":"never developed an airliner and never ran an airline."},{"time":1125000,"text":"But NASA is developing the space liner, always has,"},{"time":1129000,"text":"and runs the only space line, OK. And we've shied away from it"},{"time":1136000,"text":"because we're afraid of it. But starting back in June of 2004,"},{"time":1142000,"text":"when I showed that a little group out there actually can do it,"},{"time":1147000,"text":"can get a start with it, everything changed after that time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1150000,"text":"OK, thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1152000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}